The ring that holds the blades onto the bottom of a glass blender jar.  Waring/Hamilton Beach brand.  Not guaranteed to fit on yours - but has been successfully printed and used on mine (see photo). title: Cape for Giant Lego Darth Vader

description.text:
After printing the model, I didn't want to make a cape that wasn't printed so I drew this up.  
I have printed it on a rep 2X at 0.2mm layer height in ABS with no rafts or support material.  
It fits perfectly between his head and body and comes down all of the way to his feet (this I am pleased with as I hadn't finished printing the model before designing the cape and so had to guess on the length!  
I'll upload some photos later.
No support required. Print and fit onto your Lego Darth Vader found here: http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:50300

Five-inch (12.5 cm) wide wall mounter - I wanted to mount some wall-mountable boxes laying around in a mess. I have bought them years ago, they always slip down one from the other, from table etc. Now they are sitting gently on the wall. The mounter is inspired by the http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:8356 straight metal jacket project.

Download, print and screw it to the wall. You can choose one of two-, three- or four-part 5-inch jackets. Please print with brim atleast 5mm! The mount is too large to stick all the time to the print table. The table temperature 120-130C reccomended.

title: 12V or 24V heater for RepRap build stage

description.text:
A heater for the build stage of a RepRap 3D printer which can be made by the standard home etch technique used for making PCBs
This heater has two parallel tracks and can be wired with them in parallel for use on a 12V supply, or wired in series for a 24V supply. The resistance of 1.6 Ohms per track allows quicker heating than the commonly available types..
Two types are provided, the first, HeaterA, was designed for my own printer and has holes for spring supports and locating pins while for HeaterB these have been removed so that it can be configured for mounting holes on the corners.
I don't know if the DXF file is useful - or even if it works. I added it as Thingiverse wouldn't accept that PDF files were legitimate production files

The PCB laminate used was from Maplins as part no. FA59P, 305 x 203mm 1.6mm double sided FR4 copper weight unknown but believed to be 1oz. The laminate was sprayed with Maplins N17KH photoresist and developed with a universal PCB developer. The posative photographic transparancy was "Dataline" OHP transparancy film and was printed on a Brother MFC6510DW printer at "BEST" print setting. The back copper layer was protected with Kapton tape to prevent it from being etched.
